        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         yes you can recharm,  but it resets all resist checks as if it was an entirely new charm.</P><P>meaning if you happened to have a charm that was going to go for full duration, but you recast midway through, everything resets and the mob has a chance to break charm immediatley.</P><P>thrall of bones is far better than beguile, it has the best chance of lasting full duration. If the recast time bothers you just keep ST up, and the mob you're fighting rooted.</P><P><a href="http://tru7h.org/absor/" target="_blank">http://tru7h.org/absor/</a> -  ask absor anything!<BR><a href="http://xzzy.org/ereet/" target="_blank">http://xzzy.org/ereet/</a><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
